{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}} {{Infobox Artwork | image_file=Annibale Carracci Assumption of the Virgin.jpg | title=Assumption of the Virgin | artist=Annibale Carracci | year=1590 | medium=Oil on canvas | height_metric=130 | width_metric=97 | metric_unit=cm | imperial_unit=in | city=Madrid | museum=Museo del Prado }}
Two painting showing the [[Assumption of the Virgin Mary]] by the [[Italy|Italian]] [[Baroque]] painter [[Annibale Carracci]] was completed in 1590 and is now the [[Museo del Prado]] in [[Madrid]]. The same subject was depicted by him on the [[Assumption of the Virgin (Cerasi Chapel)|altarpiece]] of the famous [[Cerasi Chapel]] in [[Rome]].
